events.description: Roman Empire general Tiberius defeats the Dalmatae on the river Bosna.
events.html: • 8 – Roman Empire general Tiberius defeats the Dalmatae on the river Bosna.

events.description: Deposed Ecumenical Patriarch of Constantinople Nestorius, considered the originator of Nestorianism, is exiled by Roman Emperor Theodosius II to a monastery in Egypt.
events.html: • 435 – Deposed Ecumenical Patriarch of Constantinople Nestorius, considered the originator of Nestorianism, is exiled by Roman Emperor Theodosius II to a monastery in Egypt.

events.description: Battle of Saucourt-en-Vimeu: Louis III of France defeats the Vikings, an event celebrated in the poem Ludwigslied.
events.html: • 881 – Battle of Saucourt-en-Vimeu: Louis III of France defeats the Vikings, an event celebrated in the poem Ludwigslied.

events.description: Battle of Eisenach: An invading Hungarian force defeats an East Frankish army under Duke Burchard of Thuringia.
events.html: • 908 – Battle of Eisenach: An invading Hungarian force defeats an East Frankish army under Duke Burchard of Thuringia.

events.description: Olaf II of Norway is canonized as Saint Olaf by Grimketel, the English Bishop of Selsey.
events.html: • 1031 – Olaf II of Norway is canonized as Saint Olaf by Grimketel, the English Bishop of Selsey.

events.description: Frederick of Lorraine elected as Pope Stephen IX.
events.html: • 1057 – Frederick of Lorraine elected as Pope Stephen IX.

events.description: The Siege of Algeciras commences during the Spanish Reconquista.
events.html: • 1342 – The Siege of Algeciras commences during the Spanish Reconquista.

events.description: Christopher Columbus sets sail from Palos de la Frontera, Spain.
events.html: • 1492 – Christopher Columbus sets sail from Palos de la Frontera, Spain.

events.description: The first known letter from North America is sent by John Rut while at St. John's, Newfoundland.
events.html: • 1527 – The first known letter from North America is sent by John Rut while at St. John's, Newfoundland.

events.description: Long War: Austria captures Transylvania in the Battle of Goroszló.
events.html: • 1601 – Long War: Austria captures Transylvania in the Battle of Goroszló.

events.description: Thirty Years' War: The Second Battle of Nördlingen sees French forces defeating those of the Holy Roman Empire.
events.html: • 1645 – Thirty Years' War: The Second Battle of Nördlingen sees French forces defeating those of the Holy Roman Empire.

events.description: Robert LaSalle builds the Le Griffon, the first known ship built on the Great Lakes.
events.html: • 1678 – Robert LaSalle builds the Le Griffon, the first known ship built on the Great Lakes.

entities.name: René-Robert Cavelier, Sieur de La Salle

events.description: The theatre La Scala in Milan is inaugurated with the première of Antonio Salieri's Europa riconosciuta.
events.html: • 1778 – The theatre La Scala in Milan is inaugurated with the première of Antonio Salieri's Europa riconosciuta.

events.description: Treaty of Greenville is signed, ending the Northwest Indian War in the Ohio Country.
events.html: • 1795 – Treaty of Greenville is signed, ending the Northwest Indian War in the Ohio Country.

events.description: First ascent of Jungfrau, third highest summit in the Bernese Alps by brothers Johann Rudolf and Hieronymus Meyer.
events.html: • 1811 – First ascent of Jungfrau, third highest summit in the Bernese Alps by brothers Johann Rudolf and Hieronymus Meyer.

events.description: The Treaty of Lewistown is signed by the Shawnee and Seneca peoples, exchanging land in Ohio for land west of the Mississippi River.
events.html: • 1829 – The Treaty of Lewistown is signed by the Shawnee and Seneca peoples, exchanging land in Ohio for land west of the Mississippi River.[1]

events.description: Harvard University wins the first Boat Race between Yale University and Harvard. The race is also known as the first ever American intercollegiate athletic event.
events.html: • 1852 – Harvard University wins the first Boat Race between Yale University and Harvard. The race is also known as the first ever American intercollegiate athletic event.

events.description: The American Dental Association is founded in Niagara Falls, New York.
events.html: • 1859 – The American Dental Association is founded in Niagara Falls, New York.

events.description: The Firestone Tire and Rubber Company is founded.
events.html: • 1900 – The Firestone Tire and Rubber Company is founded.

events.description: Macedonian rebels in Kruševo proclaim the Kruševo Republic, which exists for only ten days before Ottoman Turks lay waste to the town.
events.html: • 1903 – Macedonian rebels in Kruševo proclaim the Kruševo Republic, which exists for only ten days before Ottoman Turks lay waste to the town.

events.description: Judge Kenesaw Mountain Landis fines Standard Oil of Indiana a record $29.4 million for illegal rebating to freight carriers; the conviction and fine are later reversed on appeal.
events.html: • 1907 – Judge Kenesaw Mountain Landis fines Standard Oil of Indiana a record $29.4 million for illegal rebating to freight carriers; the conviction and fine are later reversed on appeal.

events.description: World War I: Germany declares war against France, while Romania declares its neutrality.
events.html: • 1914 – World War I: Germany declares war against France, while Romania declares its neutrality.

events.description: Major League Baseball Commissioner Kenesaw Mountain Landis confirms the ban of the eight Chicago Black Sox, the day after they were acquitted by a Chicago court.
events.html: • 1921 – Major League Baseball Commissioner Kenesaw Mountain Landis confirms the ban of the eight Chicago Black Sox, the day after they were acquitted by a Chicago court.

events.description: Jesse Owens wins the 100 metre dash, defeating Ralph Metcalfe, at the Berlin Olympics.
events.html: • 1936 – Jesse Owens wins the 100 metre dash, defeating Ralph Metcalfe, at the Berlin Olympics.

events.description: A fire wipes out Kursha-2 in the Meshchera Lowlands, Ryazan Oblast, Russia, killing 1,200 and leaving only 20 survivors.
events.html: • 1936 – A fire wipes out Kursha-2 in the Meshchera Lowlands, Ryazan Oblast, Russia, killing 1,200 and leaving only 20 survivors.

events.description: World War II: Italian forces begin the invasion of British Somaliland.
events.html: • 1940 – World War II: Italian forces begin the invasion of British Somaliland.

events.description: Santa Claus Land, the world's first themed amusement park, opens in Santa Claus, Indiana, United States.
events.html: • 1946 – Santa Claus Land, the world's first themed amusement park, opens in Santa Claus, Indiana, United States.

events.description: Whittaker Chambers accuses Alger Hiss of being a communist and a spy for the Soviet Union.
events.html: • 1948 – Whittaker Chambers accuses Alger Hiss of being a communist and a spy for the Soviet Union.

events.description: The Basketball Association of America and the National Basketball League finalize the merger that would create the National Basketball Association.
events.html: • 1949 – The Basketball Association of America and the National Basketball League finalize the merger that would create the National Basketball Association.

events.description: The world's first nuclear submarine, the USS Nautilus, becomes the first vessel to complete a submerged transit of the geographical North Pole.
events.html: • 1958 – The world's first nuclear submarine, the USS Nautilus, becomes the first vessel to complete a submerged transit of the geographical North Pole.

events.description: Portugal's state police force PIDE fires upon striking workers in Bissau, Portuguese Guinea, killing over 50 people.
events.html: • 1959 – Portugal's state police force PIDE fires upon striking workers in Bissau, Portuguese Guinea, killing over 50 people.

events.description: Niger gains independence from France.
events.html: • 1960 – Niger gains independence from France.

events.description: The United States Senate ratifies the Anti-Ballistic Missile Treaty.
events.html: • 1972 – The United States Senate ratifies the Anti-Ballistic Missile Treaty.

events.description: A privately chartered Boeing 707 strikes a mountain peak and crashes near Agadir, Morocco, killing 188.
events.html: • 1975 – A privately chartered Boeing 707 strikes a mountain peak and crashes near Agadir, Morocco, killing 188.

events.description: Tandy Corporation announces the TRS-80, one of the world's first mass-produced personal computers.
events.html: • 1977 – Tandy Corporation announces the TRS-80, one of the world's first mass-produced personal computers.

events.description: Senegalese opposition parties, under the leadership of Mamadou Dia, launch the Antiimperialist Action Front

entities.name: Antiimperialist Action Front – Suxxali Reew Mi

events.description: Oued El-Had and Mezouara massacre in Algeria: A total of 116 villagers killed, 40 in Oued El-Had and 76 in Mezouara.
events.html: • 1997 – Oued El-Had and Mezouara massacre in Algeria: A total of 116 villagers killed, 40 in Oued El-Had and 76 in Mezouara.

events.description: The tallest free-standing structure in the Southern Hemisphere, Sky Tower in downtown Auckland, New Zealand, opens after two-and-a-half years of construction.

events.description: The pedestal of the Statue of Liberty reopens after being closed since the September 11 attacks.
events.html: • 2004 – The pedestal of the Statue of Liberty reopens after being closed since the September 11 attacks.

events.description: Widespread rioting erupts in Karachi, Pakistan, after the assassination of a local politician, leaving at least 85 dead and at least 17 billion Pakistani rupees (US$200 million) in damage.

events.html: • 2014 – The genocide of Yazidis by ISIL begins.[4]

events.html: • 2018 – Two burka-clad men kill 29 people and injure more than 80 in a suicide attack on a Shia mosque in eastern Afghanistan.[5]
